\n`K₁ : HomologicalComplex C₁ c₁`, `K₂ : HomologicalComplex C₂ c₂` and\n`K₃ : HomologicalComplex C₃ c₃`, and complexes shapes `c₁₂`, `c₄`, this asserts\nthat for all `i₁₂ : ι₁₂` and `i₃ : ι₃`, the functor `G(-, K₃.X i₃)` commutes with\nthe coproducts of the `F₁₂(X₁ i₁, X₂ i₂)` such that `π c₁ c₂ c₁₂ ⟨i₁, i₂⟩ = i₁₂`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/BifunctorAssociator.html#HomologicalComplex.HasGoodTrifunctor₁₂Obj","kind":"def","line":71,"name":"HomologicalComplex.HasGoodTrifunctor₁₂Obj","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/BifunctorAssociator.lean#L71-L78"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.GradedObject.Associator","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Linear.LinearFunctor","Mathlib.Algebra.Homology.Bifunctor"],"instances":[{"className":"CategoryTheory.Limits.HasColimit","name":"HomologicalComplex.instHasMapProdObjGradedObjectFunctorMapBifunctorXπ","typeNames":["CategoryTheory.GradedObject.mapObjFun"]},{"className":"CategoryTheory.Limits.HasColimit","name":"HomologicalComplex.instHasMapProdObjGradedObjectFunctorMapBifunctorMapBifunctorMapObjπX","typeNames":["CategoryTheory.GradedObject.mapObjFun"]},{"className":"CategoryTheory.Limits.HasColimit","name":"HomologicalComplex.instHasMapProdObjGradedObjectFunctorMapBifunctorXMapBifunctorMapObjπ","typeNames":["CategoryTheory.GradedObject.mapObjFun"]}],"name":"Mathlib.Algebra.Homology.BifunctorAssociator"}